The Standardised Precipitation Index (SPI) was calculated using the R package 'SPEI' (Beguería et al., 2014) using daily precipitation data from the Newport weather station over 21 years (1995 - 2016). (Beguería, S., Vicente-Serrano, S.M., Reig, F., and Latorre, B.: Standardized precipitation evapotranspiration index (SPEI) revisited: parameter fitting, evapotranspiration models, tools, datasets and drought monitoring, Int. J. Climatol., 34 (10), 3001–3023, 2014.)
1 (drought) when SPI was<-1.5. Not drought (0) when SPI >-1.5

Water levels (cm) were recorded every 15 minutes at each site using OTT Hydrometry Orpheus Mini water level loggers. No reliable rating curve was available for the Black river, discharge was estimated using the drainage area ratio method based on the Glenamong discharge (Hirsch, 1979). (Hirsch, R.M.: An evaluation of some record reconstruction techniques, Water Resour. Res., 15 (6): 1781–1790 https://agupubs.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/pdf/10.1029/WR015i006p01781, 1979.)

Water levels (cm) were recorded every 15 minutes at each site using OTT Hydrometry Orpheus Mini water level loggers. The level was converted to volume of discharge (m3) using a site specific ratings curves
